Dear all,

I have just posted a paper on the use of classes in category theory.

https://arxiv.org/abs/1801.08528

Abstract:

We examine the use of classes to formulate several categorical notions.
This leads to two proposals: an explicit structure for working with
subobjects, and a hierarchy of k-classes. We apply the latter to both
ordinary and higher categories.

Any comments would be welcome.

Paul


